properties.Name: StockAuthorizedShares
properties.Description:
Also called "authorized stock", it is the maximum number of shares of any class that a corporation may issue. 

This amount is set at the time of incorporation and is part of the Articles of Incorporation. A corporation provides for future increases in authorized stock by the votes of stockholders. 

The corporation does not have to issue all the authorized shares.

Columns.Name: StockId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Financial Product.

Columns.Name: Date
Columns.Description: The date that the authorized shares were issued.

Columns.Name: NumberOfAuthorizedShares
Columns.Description: The number of shares authorized for sale or issue.

Columns.Name: NumberSharesIssued
Columns.Description: The number of shares actually issued.

Columns.Name: PublicFloatNumberOfShares
Columns.Description: The portion of the issued stock not held by affiliates (insiders) of the public company.
